body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Car Deals Plus. My name is Eric Washington.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: May I please have your name?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Natalie. Before we proceed, can you please provide me with your telephone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: My telephone number is five five five, two two two, three three three three.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. As we work on resolving the issue, could you also provide me with your email address?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Yes, my email address is natalie.jenkins@example.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, I have noted down your contact details. Thank you for sharing, Natalie.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: We will investigate the quality concern at the dealership. I appreciate your patience and understanding.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for reaching out, Natalie. Have a great day!
